    <label for="inbrief-checkbox">
        <span class="label-personal">Personal Mode</span>
        <span class="switch"></span>
        <span class="label-recruiter">Recruiter Mode</span>
    </label>
    <div class="content-personal">
        <p>
            Hey there! I‚Äôm Ben, a software dev from Charleston SC, USA, learning
            how cold the northeast can be. You can call me a ‚Äútraditional‚Äù
            software developer by trade given my <a
                href="https://www.cc.gatech.edu/degree-programs/bachelor-science-computer-science"
                >BS in CS</a
            > from Georgia Tech (go Jackets!). Today, I‚Äôve channeled this technical
            know-how into open source web development as a full-time maintainer at
            <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            My core values are <strong
                >be caring, be clear, and be casual.</strong
            > Tech is a scary industry to jump into, especially without a sense of
            humor to keep your head on straight. So as long as I‚Äôm a web developer,
            my goal is to <a href="#i-teach">teach</a> and <a href="#i-create"
                >build</a
            > tools that help others become the best version of themselves. Well,
            assuming we adhere to <a href="https://semver.org/"
                >semantic versioning principles</a
            > üòâ
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="content-recruiter">
        <p>
